            <div type="glosses">
                <note xml:id="BLENHEIMGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Blenheim&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The village of Blenheim 
                    on the Danube, where, on 13 August 1704, the English defeated French and Bavarian forces, 
                    leading ultimately to the Treaty of Utrecht in 1713 that secured British colonial expansion. 
                    The victory dealt a blow to the cause of the young Pretender, recognized by France, 
                    and the increased British trading strength enabled Parliament to dictate terms 
                    to the Scots in the 1707 Act of Union.</p></note><!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_contextual" target="filename_glosses.php#SOMETHINGUNIQUEGLOSS"/>.-->

                <note xml:id="WATERLOOGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Waterloo&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The decisive British victory over Napoleon.</p></note><!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_contextual" target="filename_glosses.php#ALSOSOMETHINGUNIQUEGLOSS"/>.-->
                
                <note xml:id="MARLBOROUGHGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Marlborough&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>John Churchill, earl of Marlborough, 
                    who commanded the forces at Blenheim. As a result of this and other victories, 
                    he was rewarded with the title of duke and Blenheim Palace, designed by John Vanbrugh.</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="TALLARDGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Marshal TALLARD&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>???</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="HASTINGSGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;hastings&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The defeat 
                    of Saxon Harold in 1066 by William, duke of Normandy.</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="BANNOCKBURNGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Bannockburn&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The boggy ground where, 
                    in 1314, the army of Edward II, successor to Edward I, “the Hammer of the Scots,” 
                    was trapped and massacred by Scottish forces under Robert Bruce.</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="BOHUNGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Bohun&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>???</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="BANNOCKBURNGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Cressys fight&#x201C;
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIII">MS III</title>)&#x2014;</hi>At Crécy, 
                    in 1346 during Edward III’s campaign in France, the king’s son Edward, the Black Prince, 
                    distinguished himself. He was knighted on the battlefield, and adopted the motto 
                    “Ich dien” (“I serve”) of the fallen king of Bohemia.</p></note>
